Hip and affordable apartment of 31 m2 located within the Ring. This is a unique opportunity! Are you looking for a home in a good location and that is Ready-to-use? Then this nice apartment is for you! The home is located on the 4th floor, completed in 2015 and neatly finished with a modern kitchen and bathroom.

This former GAK building underwent a transformation into a residential building. The apartment is located in the south wing of this building "De Studio Part II". There is a double elevator, a caretaker, a locked bicycle shed and a shared laundry room, where (Miele) washing machines and dryers are at your disposal.

Layout:
Entrance with videophone installation and secure tag system (both at the main entrance and on the floor), neat kitchen with a wooden worktop with ceramic hob, combi oven, extractor hood and it is quite easy to create a connection for the washing machine / dryer. Bathroom with shower, floating toilet and sink. Living room with windows across the entire width, a lovely light space, enough space for a (folding) bed. Laminate flooring throughout the house. Heat recovery system to save on your heating costs. Well-insulated energy-efficient home. Underfloor heating and cooling available. Pre-connection for internet via fibre optic and cable.

Location:
The many restaurants, bars and shops in the area make you feel at home immediately. Opposite the entrance to the complex is the Bos en Lommer city park, a great place to relax, just like the wide jetty of the Erasmusgracht on the side of the building. A little further on you will also find the Erasmus Park where fun events are organised in the summer. For your daily shopping you can go to the adjacent Bos en Lommerplein.

Accessibility:
The accessibility is excellent: the complex is very conveniently located near the A10 and Amsterdam-Sloterdijk train station. There are various bus and tram stops in front of the door (including tram 7 and 14 and bus 15, 21 and 80). By bike you can reach the city centre, the Jordaan or the canals in 10-15 minutes. A parking permit is not possible. There is a parking lot behind the complex where it is possible to rent a space via parkingYou.

Ground lease:
This concerns municipal ground lease. The annual lease for the apartment is € 635,04 and is in principle deductible from income tax for owner-occupied. End of period (30-11-2063) and the General Provisions 2000 apply with an annual indexation.

Home Owners' association:
The V.v.E. is healthy, active and is professionally managed by VvE Beheer Amsterdam. The service costs are € 133,16 per month and the advance payment for city heating € 36,78. The administrator is responsible for the financial and administrative management, administrative and technical support.

Details:
- Living area of 31 m2 (according to NEN 2580);
- Studio;
- Modern and trendy complex with elevator, caretaker, laundry room and bicycle shed;
- 4th floor;
- Active home owners' association;
- Well insulated;
- Energy label A;
- The building is in the procedure to be designated as a municipal monument;
- Underfloor heating and cooling;
- A parking permit is not possible, there are parking spaces for rent behind the building via ParkingYou;
- Favorably located with regard to arterial roads;
- Delivery in consultation.

